No!

1091
01:42:56,080 --> 01:42:57,520
- No. Wait!
- Father!

1092
01:43:00,040 --> 01:43:02,028
We are live here at
St. Peter's Square...

1093
01:43:02,080 --> 01:43:05,400
where, despite a bomb threat,
and an orderly evacuation,

1094
01:43:05,452 --> 01:43:08,028
the crowd is actually growing in size.

1095
01:43:08,080 --> 01:43:10,880
As we await an official announcement
from the Vatican spokesman

1096
01:43:10,932 --> 01:43:12,908
as to the exact nature of the threat

1097
01:43:12,960 --> 01:43:15,960
and whether or not they are
treating it as a credible danger...

1098
01:43:24,080 --> 01:43:25,000
This way!

1099
01:43:54,160 --> 01:43:55,400
He's got a bomb with him.

1100
01:43:56,640 --> 01:43:57,680
A bomb?

1101
01:44:02,960 --> 01:44:05,520
Roberto, this is an emergency.
I'll take her up alone.

1102
01:44:10,200 --> 01:44:12,280
He's got clearance.

1103
01:44:35,800 --> 01:44:38,360
Oh, my God.

1104
01:46:34,920 --> 01:46:36,560
Get down!

1105
01:49:21,840 --> 01:49:23,160
Cardinal Strauss?

1106
01:49:23,960 --> 01:49:27,520
It was the Camerlengo.
He has saved us all.

1107
01:49:28,120 --> 01:49:31,240
He has saved the Church
and he's still alive.

1108
01:49:32,600 --> 01:49:34,600
Praise God. Praise God.

1109
01:49:39,880 --> 01:49:41,120
He is alive.

1110
01:49:41,640 --> 01:49:44,360
He sacrificed himself for all of us.

1111
01:50:11,560 --> 01:50:14,360
You know the worst thing
we thought would happen

1112
01:50:15,520 --> 01:50:18,840
was that our work would fall into
the hands of the energy companies.

1113
01:50:21,560 --> 01:50:23,280
We thought we could change the world.

1114
01:50:24,160 --> 01:50:27,960
- So naive.
- No, not naive.

1115
01:50:29,080 --> 01:50:30,560
Innocent, maybe.

1116
01:50:31,120 --> 01:50:33,240
But it's not a crime.

1117
01:50:34,720 --> 01:50:36,080
I'm not so sure.

1118
01:50:38,160 --> 01:50:39,920
Go back to work.

1119
01:50:41,120 --> 01:50:42,680
Change the world.

1120
01:51:02,760 --> 01:51:08,400
A gift, uh, you understand?
Let's say for Catholics everywhere.

1121
01:51:08,600 --> 01:51:11,240
The Carmelengo's age
shouldn't influence the decision.

1122
01:51:11,440 --> 01:51:14,220
Signori, you are no doubt
aware that by Holy Law

1123
01:51:14,272 --> 01:51:17,000
the man is inelligible
for election to the papacy.

1124
01:51:17,360 --> 01:51:19,320
He's not a cardinal.
He's a priest.

1125
01:51:19,372 --> 01:51:20,600
He's of insufficient age.

1126
01:51:20,800 --> 01:51:23,680
Or maybe there's a way we
could consider the possibility.

1127
01:51:23,880 --> 01:51:27,840
I am sorry. The protocols of conclave
are not subject to modification.

1128
01:51:28,000 --> 01:51:30,840
I will not call a ballot on this matter.

1129
01:51:31,040 --> 01:51:33,600
But, signore, you
would not hold a ballot.

1130
01:51:33,800 --> 01:51:37,200
Surely, you remember? You gave
up your post as Great Elector.

1131
01:51:37,920 --> 01:51:40,080
They are singing at St. Peter's Square.

1132
01:51:40,240 --> 01:51:42,880
Now, what happened here
tonight transcends our laws.

1133
01:51:43,120 --> 01:51:47,360
Has it? Is it God's will that
we give ourselves over to frenzy?

1134
01:51:47,440 --> 01:51:48,880
Discard the rules of the Church?

1135
01:51:48,920 --> 01:51:51,120
Perhaps we need not discard them.

1136
01:51:52,160 --> 01:51:57,760
Signori, I am thinking now of Romano
Pontifici Eligendo numero 60...

1137
01:51:58,000 --> 01:52:00,880
- Acclamation by Adoration.
- Exactly, signore. Exactly.

1138
01:52:01,160 --> 01:52:03,600
Yes. If the Holy Spirit
speaks through us,

1139
01:52:04,120 --> 01:52:06,040
and we call a man's name out loud...

1140
01:52:06,240 --> 01:52:08,960
That is election by adoration.

1141
01:52:09,400 --> 01:52:11,240
- Yes.
- He's God's choice.

1142
01:52:11,520 --> 01:52:17,240
Yes. And the candidate need only be
an ordained member of the clergy,

1143
01:52:17,292 --> 01:52:21,320
present in the Sistine Chapel
at the moment of his election.

1144
01:52:53,080 --> 01:52:55,308
- Signor Camerlengo?
- Yes?

1145
01:52:55,360 --> 01:52:58,840
The cardinals ask you to join them
in conclave as soon as possible.

1146
01:52:58,960 --> 01:53:01,440
- Me?
- Yes, Padre.

1147
01:53:24,520 --> 01:53:25,960
What are you doing?

1148
01:53:26,000 --> 01:53:28,360
Silvano's journals. I want them back.

1149
01:53:52,560 --> 01:53:54,040
Richter said...

1150
01:53:55,360 --> 01:53:57,680
His Holiness suffered from seizures

1151
01:53:57,720 --> 01:54:00,200
and steps were taken...

1152
01:54:00,440 --> 01:54:02,320
for safety.

1153
01:54:06,320 --> 01:54:08,880
He made sure he was watched, he said.

1154
01:54:10,960 --> 01:54:13,880
What if he were trying
to give me this key?

1155
01:54:15,040 --> 01:54:17,040
That's the Papal office.

1156
01:54:17,440 --> 01:54:19,308
If the Pope was worried about seizures,

1157
01:54:19,360 --> 01:54:22,280
he must've had Richter install
cameras without telling anyone.

1158
01:54:22,320 --> 01:54:25,120
To keep an eye on him for his safety.

1159
01:54:26,880 --> 01:54:28,880
Maybe it records.

1160
01:54:38,920 --> 01:54:43,560
- I read the journals, Patrick.
- The scientist kept journals. So?

1161
01:54:43,612 --> 01:54:46,920
- You figure prominently in them.
- Really?

1162
01:54:46,960 --> 01:54:51,560
The Devoli wasn't just a physicist.
He was also a Catholic priest.

1163
01:54:52,240 --> 01:54:56,400
As such, he was deeply conflicted
about the implications of his work

1164
01:54:56,452 --> 01:54:58,440
and in need of spiritual guidance.

1165
01:54:58,492 --> 01:55:00,200
Like Galileo.

1166
01:55:01,040 --> 01:55:02,788
About a month ago,

1167
01:55:02,840 --> 01:55:05,200
he requested an
audience with the Pope.

1168
01:55:05,252 --> 01:55:06,120
But you know that,

1169
01:55:06,320 --> 01:55:09,600
cause you granted the audience and
you were also present during it.

1170
01:55:09,652 --> 01:55:12,708
The 'God Particle'. To actually
claim an act of creation.

1171
01:55:12,760 --> 01:55:17,160
- The blasphemy. The arrogance.
- The Holy Father didn't see it like that.

1172
01:55:17,240 --> 01:55:19,308
He urged him to go public.

1173
01:55:19,360 --> 01:55:22,080
His Holiness thought that
the discovery could actually

1174
01:55:22,160 --> 01:55:25,380
scientifically prove the
existence of a divine power.

1175
01:55:25,432 --> 01:55:28,600
And begin to bridge the gap
between science and religion.

1176
01:55:28,652 --> 01:55:31,200
His work was not religious.
It was sacrilegious.

1177
01:55:31,240 --> 01:55:32,040
But you...

1178
01:55:32,920 --> 01:55:36,680
You saw the pope's position
as a softening of church law.

1179
01:55:36,732 --> 01:55:40,480
As an old man's weakness.
Your father's weakness.

1180
01:55:40,520 --> 01:55:42,420
You murdered the Vicar of Christ.

1181
01:55:42,472 --> 01:55:44,320
He raised me to
protect this Church,

1182
01:55:44,372 --> 01:55:45,920
even from within.

1183
01:55:47,680 --> 01:55:52,240
Then you conjured up an old enemy
from the past. The Illuminati.

1184
01:55:52,280 --> 01:55:54,800
You found the ancient brands
in the papal vaults

1185
01:55:54,852 --> 01:55:57,326
and put them to use
to spread fear!

1186
01:55:57,378 --> 01:55:59,800
The Cardinals are men of belief.

1187
01:55:59,840 --> 01:56:03,800
Right now, their belief
in evil is uniting them.

1188
01:56:03,840 --> 01:56:06,800
The entire Catholic world
will be united by this attack.

1189
01:56:06,852 --> 01:56:08,400
There is no attack.

1190
01:56:09,360 --> 01:56:12,600
You're trying to convince the
Cardinals they're in a war,

1191
01:56:12,652 --> 01:56:14,440
so they will choose a
warrior to lead them.

1192
01:56:14,492 --> 01:56:15,828
We are at war.

1193
01:56:15,880 --> 01:56:17,868
We're weak when we should be strong.

1194
01:56:17,920 --> 01:56:21,800
If science is allowed to
claim the power of creation,

1195
01:56:21,840 --> 01:56:23,600
what is left for God?

1196
01:56:23,640 --> 01:56:25,560
It didn't work, Patrick.

1197
01:56:26,240 --> 01:56:29,200
- It isn't finished.
- Oh yes, it's finished.

1198
01:56:31,480 --> 01:56:32,880
It's finished.

1199
01:56:33,760 --> 01:56:36,440
I've shown the journals
to Father Simeon.

1200
01:56:36,492 --> 01:56:38,886
The moment the doors
to the Conclave open,

1201
01:56:38,938 --> 01:56:41,280
he will tell the Cardinals
what you've done.

1202
01:56:42,200 --> 01:56:44,400
I was planning on doing this alone.

1203
01:56:47,680 --> 01:56:48,840
Put it down.

1204
01:56:51,880 --> 01:56:53,880
But, perhaps,
it's better that you're here.

1205
01:56:53,920 --> 01:56:55,320
Put it down.

1206
01:56:57,200 --> 01:56:58,960
Put it away.

1207
01:57:10,040 --> 01:57:13,600
Help. He's the one.
He's got a gun.

1208
01:57:17,280 --> 01:57:19,680
- Illuminatus!
- You bastard.

1209
01:57:20,040 --> 01:57:20,800
Illuminatus!

1210
01:57:20,840 --> 01:57:21,960
You bastard!

1211
01:57:26,040 --> 01:57:27,160
Padre.

1212
01:57:37,040 --> 01:57:40,240
And get the helicopter for
the older cardinals, right?

1213
01:58:29,680 --> 01:58:32,200
I've been summoned by
the College of Cardinals.

1214
01:59:42,240 --> 01:59:43,560
Gently.

1215
01:59:43,880 --> 01:59:45,240
But within our walls.

1216
01:59:57,360 --> 01:59:59,840
He's on your side.

1217
02:00:46,160 --> 02:00:50,080
Father, into thy hands
I commend my spirit.

1218
02:01:37,960 --> 02:01:42,560
Church sources now confirm that
Carmelengo, Father Patrick McKenna,

1219
02:01:42,612 --> 02:01:46,600
